Modou Barrow has joined Nottingham Forest on loan from Swansea City until the end of the season.

Swansea manager Garry Monk was keen for the winger to get first-team football having seen Jefferson Montero return from his hamstring injury.

The 22-year-old has impressed significantly since joining from Swedish club Ostersunds last September and quickly landed an improved four-year contract last month.

