Club staff have been surprised by his progress, but having made only one Premier League start this season it has been deemed necessary to send him to the Championship club for extra experience.

Forest boss Dougie Freedman took Barrow on trial at Bolton last summer, but was unsuccessful in an attempt to sign him. 

